4) Simulated annealing\
    a) Simulated annealing uses decreases levels of random stochastic behaviour to \'91escape\'92 from local \
	minima. Large random values at the start allow the current node to find its way out of larger local minima, \
	and as the randomness decreases, it eventually ends up at the very bottom of the global minimum.\
